    <div class="article-intro"><div class="article-hero"><img src="/assets/screens/en-economy-720.webp" width="1280" height="720" alt="VeVolt charging cost and savings screen" fetchpriority="high"></div><header class="article-header"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>VeVolt guide</p><h1>How much does it cost to charge an electric car?</h1><p class="lede">Charging cost is not one fixed number. It depends on how many kilowatt-hours enter the battery, the local tariff and any fees charged by the station or parking facility.</p><p class="article-meta">Updated 18/07/2026 · 9 min read</p></header></div>
    <div class="article-layout"><div class="article-body"><section><h2>Use kilowatt-hours as the starting point</h2><p>Multiply the energy added in kWh by the price per kWh. If you only know the battery percentage, estimate the fraction of the usable battery capacity that needs to be restored.</p></section><section><h2>Include the complete cost</h2><p>Allow for charging losses and check session, idle, membership and parking fees. A location advertising free energy can still have a meaningful parking cost.</p><ul><li>Energy delivered in kWh</li><li>Price per kWh</li><li>Charging losses</li><li>Session or idle fee</li><li>Parking charge</li></ul></section><section><h2>Compare trips, not isolated prices</h2><p>Record energy and amount paid after each session. A small history gives a more realistic cost per kilometer than a single ideal calculation.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Is public charging always more expensive than home charging?</summary><p>Not always, but public fast charging often includes infrastructure and service costs that can raise the price.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can VeVolt charge me for electricity?</summary><p>No. VeVolt helps organize information and records; payment is handled by the charger operator or venue.</p></details></div></section></div>
    <aside class="article-aside"><h2>Use VeVolt in your routine</h2><p>Find chargers, check reports, plan alternatives and record your experience in one app.</p><a class="button primary" href="/en/testers">Join the test</a><h2>Sources and further reading</h2><ul class="source-list"><li><a href="https://www.gov.br/aneel/pt-br/assuntos/veiculos-eletricos" rel="noopener noreferrer">ANEEL - Electric vehicles and charging rules</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gov.br/inmetro/pt-br/acesso-a-informacao/perguntas-frequentes/avaliacao-da-conformidade/etiquetagem-para-veiculos-leves/como-e-calculado-o-consumo-dos-carros-eletricos" rel="noopener noreferrer">Inmetro - How electric-vehicle consumption is calculated</a></li></ul></aside></div>
